WEBVTT

00:27.500 --> 00:29.500
[pensive instrumental music playing]

01:27.541 --> 01:30.250
Mother has a surprise for you
waiting up ahead.

01:32.375 --> 01:33.583
A surprise?

01:34.291 --> 01:36.041
A birthday surprise.

01:49.333 --> 01:52.291
Norma Jeane. Look.

01:53.125 --> 01:54.958
That man is your father.

01:57.750 --> 01:58.791
My father?

02:00.291 --> 02:01.208
He's my father?

02:01.291 --> 02:05.208
[shushes] Look. Your father.

02:12.791 --> 02:14.416
His name is a beautiful name.

02:16.625 --> 02:18.000
And an important name.

02:20.125 --> 02:21.750
But it's a name I can't utter.

02:35.541 --> 02:36.416
No!

02:39.708 --> 02:41.750
You mustn't touch with sticky fingers.

02:44.625 --> 02:45.875
So no one knows.

02:47.500 --> 02:50.375
And no one must know,
even that you've seen this.

02:52.416 --> 02:55.083
There are complications
in both our lives, you see?

02:56.041 --> 02:58.791
When you were born,
your father was far away.

02:59.625 --> 03:03.208
He's at a great distance, even now,
and I worry for his safety.

03:05.333 --> 03:08.375
But in our hearts, we're wed.

03:09.625 --> 03:11.208
We're husband and wife.

03:14.333 --> 03:17.083
Though we scorn convention
and will not acquiesce to it.

03:19.791 --> 03:21.833
But where is he?

03:22.708 --> 03:24.291
[fly buzzing]

03:25.416 --> 03:28.000
[telephone ringing]

03:28.500 --> 03:31.291
Mmm. My hands are shaking.

03:33.625 --> 03:37.250
Is this room vibrating?

03:40.250 --> 03:46.083
In California, you… can't tell
what's "real" and what's "just yourself."

03:50.041 --> 03:52.791
-[ringing continues]
-[mother sighs]

03:55.375 --> 03:58.083
[exhales] Looks delicious, doesn't it?

03:58.166 --> 03:59.958
-[liquid pouring]
-[mother chuckles]

04:18.000 --> 04:19.875
So you don't drool on my cover.

04:28.333 --> 04:29.208
[chuckles softly]

04:30.375 --> 04:33.666
Do you remember, Norma Jeane,
who used to sleep here?

04:33.750 --> 04:36.125
In this drawer? Do you remember?

04:39.083 --> 04:40.083
[Norma Jeane groans]

04:41.000 --> 04:42.333
You! [chuckles]

04:42.416 --> 04:45.500
You, Norma Jeane!
You slept right in this very drawer.

04:47.500 --> 04:49.875
We were so poor,
this drawer was your crib.

04:52.916 --> 04:55.000
But it was good enough for us, wasn't it?

04:57.458 --> 05:01.166
["Für Elise" playing slowly on piano]

05:21.666 --> 05:23.375
[father] I love you, Norma Jeane.

05:24.875 --> 05:28.541
And one day,
I will return to Los Angeles to claim you.

05:38.041 --> 05:41.750
[mother] Norma Jeane? Norma Jeane?

05:44.333 --> 05:45.833
Norma Jeane, honey. Wake up!

05:47.833 --> 05:48.833
Wake up!

05:49.583 --> 05:52.000
Come on. Up, up! Let's go!

05:54.500 --> 05:57.166
-[Norma Jeane] I'm tired.
-[mother] Come with me.

06:03.791 --> 06:04.708
Okay.

06:06.875 --> 06:07.916
[door thuds]

06:12.250 --> 06:13.666
[fire crackling]

06:21.250 --> 06:23.041
[siren wailing]

06:24.875 --> 06:26.708
[indistinct shouting]

06:31.833 --> 06:33.000
[car starts]

06:38.500 --> 06:40.833
[horns honking]

06:49.458 --> 06:50.916
[car horn honks]

06:55.083 --> 06:57.583
Stop squirming like
a little snake needing to pee.

06:59.916 --> 07:04.750
Mother? What if the house burns down?
I forgot my tiger.

07:04.833 --> 07:06.166
[Mother] That toy.

07:07.000 --> 07:09.333
-[car horn honks]
-[man] Go back!

07:17.291 --> 07:19.708
[dramatic music playing]

07:22.916 --> 07:25.750
[mother] Oh God. Oh God.

07:25.833 --> 07:28.208
Oh God, I can't see a fucking thing.

07:34.208 --> 07:36.583
[indistinct shouting]

07:38.375 --> 07:41.916
[officer] Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

07:42.000 --> 07:42.833
Hey!

07:50.166 --> 07:51.583
What the hell are you doing?

07:53.250 --> 07:54.541
[exhales]

07:54.625 --> 07:58.166
We've been invited to a private residence
at the top of Laurel Canyon.

07:58.250 --> 08:03.000
The owner has a fireproof mansion.
My daughter and I will be safe there.

08:03.083 --> 08:07.875
I can't say this man's name, officer,
but it's a name you all know.

08:07.958 --> 08:09.833
He's a titan in the industry.

08:11.750 --> 08:13.416
This little girl is his daughter.

08:14.250 --> 08:16.833
This is a city of sand,
nothing will long endure,

08:16.916 --> 08:18.375
but we are going.

08:19.375 --> 08:20.958
Ma'am, go home.

08:21.041 --> 08:23.916
Put your little girl to bed, okay?
It's late.

08:26.625 --> 08:29.250
Actually, officer,
I'd like to see hell close-up.

08:30.125 --> 08:31.208
A preview.

08:34.125 --> 08:37.291
Ma'am, you need to turn around.

08:37.375 --> 08:40.375
I can give you an escort
if you need one, but this is an order.

08:40.458 --> 08:42.750
If you don't turn around,
I'll have to put you under arrest.

08:42.833 --> 08:45.416
Under arrest for driving my car?

08:56.416 --> 08:58.708
I'm sorry, officer.
Please don't arrest me.

09:01.875 --> 09:04.875
[scoffs] I wish you would shoot me.

09:13.291 --> 09:14.750
Lady, look, go home, okay?

09:14.833 --> 09:18.375
You're drunk, you're doped up,
and no one's got time for this tonight.

09:18.458 --> 09:21.375
You're saying things
to get you into trouble.

09:21.458 --> 09:23.166
[chuckles softly]

09:23.250 --> 09:24.416
[officer] Come on. Go.

09:25.791 --> 09:27.041
[car starts]

09:46.583 --> 09:47.750
[mother grunts]

09:50.666 --> 09:52.333
[breathing heavily]

09:53.500 --> 09:54.833
[gear shifts]

10:03.875 --> 10:05.041
[mother grunts]

10:18.416 --> 10:21.208
Mother? Was he here?

10:21.291 --> 10:24.333
My father? All this time?

10:24.416 --> 10:26.000
Why didn't he come to see us?

10:27.125 --> 10:28.583
[sobs softly]

10:30.500 --> 10:33.708
What? What?

10:37.750 --> 10:40.083
-[Norma Jeane grunts, cries]
-[mother yelling]

10:41.875 --> 10:43.291
[sobbing]

10:45.458 --> 10:47.458
[mother sniffles and sobs]

10:57.416 --> 10:58.833
[Norma Jeane] It's too hot.

11:03.666 --> 11:05.125
Norma Jeane, get in the bath.

11:06.291 --> 11:08.083
Be a good girl and get in the bath.

11:12.916 --> 11:14.708
[inhales sharply]

11:14.791 --> 11:17.333
-[Norma Jeane] It's too hot.
-Get in the bath!

11:18.708 --> 11:20.541
[both sobbing]

11:23.250 --> 11:26.208
Good girl. Good girl. Okay.

11:27.250 --> 11:33.041
[woman] Because she loved the child
and wished to spare her grief.

11:34.833 --> 11:39.166
Because the child
was her own secret self, exposed.

11:40.291 --> 11:42.625
[mother shouting distortedly]

11:46.583 --> 11:51.083
[woman] Because the very father
of the child had wished it not to be born.

11:51.166 --> 11:52.791
[mother exclaims]

11:54.875 --> 11:58.750
[woman] Because he had given her money,
scattering bills across the bed.

12:01.666 --> 12:04.250
Because he told her
he had never loved her.

12:05.208 --> 12:07.208
She had misunderstood.

12:09.166 --> 12:11.500
Because before the pregnancy,
he had loved her.

12:14.333 --> 12:16.000
And after, he had not.

12:20.291 --> 12:23.166
Because he would have married her.
She was certain.

12:23.250 --> 12:25.208
[mother sobbing]

12:25.291 --> 12:26.166
[coughing]

12:26.250 --> 12:30.166
[woman] Because no one
could love a child so accursed.

12:31.291 --> 12:32.541
It's because of you!

12:33.541 --> 12:37.250
You're the reason he went away!
He didn't want you!

12:38.375 --> 12:40.000
-[fire blazing]
-[mother screams]

12:40.083 --> 12:41.416
[objects crashing]

12:45.750 --> 12:47.416
Help! Help us!

12:48.458 --> 12:51.541
-[doorbell ringing]
-Help! Help us!

12:54.250 --> 12:55.708
Help, my mother's sick!

12:55.791 --> 12:57.750
-Norma Jeane?
-[Norma Jeane] Help my mother.

12:57.833 --> 13:00.333
Clive, bring her in. Cover her.

13:00.416 --> 13:01.708
Come here.

13:01.791 --> 13:03.291
Come here, Norma Jeane.

13:03.375 --> 13:06.875
-There's something wrong with your mother?
-She needs help.

13:08.000 --> 13:09.791
-She needs help?
-[objects crashing]

13:14.416 --> 13:15.416
[door shuts]

13:16.708 --> 13:19.083
You come inside with me, Norma Jeane.

13:19.166 --> 13:22.666
-You wait right here. Okay?
-[piano playing erratically]

13:22.750 --> 13:24.083
You just stay with me.

13:24.166 --> 13:26.500
You're okay. You're okay now.

13:27.500 --> 13:28.875
You're safe, Norma Jeane.

13:30.875 --> 13:32.166
[shushes]

13:35.208 --> 13:38.291
Your mama's well enough
to see you now, Norma Jeane.

13:41.208 --> 13:42.916
Your mama's been askin' for you.

13:44.916 --> 13:47.625
The doctors say she's well enough
for you to visit her.

13:48.541 --> 13:49.458
Shall we go?

13:54.125 --> 13:55.125
Where is she?

13:59.333 --> 14:01.000
She's in the hospital in Norwalk.

14:04.291 --> 14:06.125
Sh… she's better now?

14:08.541 --> 14:11.000
Well, she's well enough
for you to visit with her.

14:23.583 --> 14:25.833
Uncle Clive is gonna take us in the car.

14:26.750 --> 14:29.375
And I'm gonna put a few things
in a suitcase for you.

14:30.250 --> 14:31.750
You don't have to do anything.

14:34.458 --> 14:35.291
Okay.

15:10.000 --> 15:11.708
[breathing shakily]

15:17.958 --> 15:19.166
[car thuds]

15:29.333 --> 15:30.458
[car stops]

15:34.750 --> 15:35.750
[car door closes]

15:48.291 --> 15:50.041
Please forgive me, Norma Jeane.

15:51.500 --> 15:53.625
There's no other place for you right now.

15:54.500 --> 15:55.583
Your mother is sick.

15:56.625 --> 15:59.000
The doctors say that she is very sick.

16:00.500 --> 16:01.875
She tried to hurt you.

16:03.375 --> 16:05.500
She can't be a mother to you just now.

16:06.875 --> 16:09.750
I can't be a mother to you just now.

16:12.250 --> 16:13.916
[crying] But I'm not an orphan.

16:14.541 --> 16:17.541
I have a mother, and I have a father.

16:18.458 --> 16:19.791
I'm not an orphan.

16:20.541 --> 16:24.125
My father is coming home soon.
He promised.

16:26.375 --> 16:30.500
[woman] Come on now, Norma Jeane.
Come on. Be a good girl. Be a good girl.

16:30.583 --> 16:31.750
[Norma Jeane sobs] No!

16:33.583 --> 16:35.541
[woman] Please, Norma Jeane? Please?

16:35.625 --> 16:38.708
-[Norma Jeane] No! I'm not an orphan!
-Stop it! Come on!

16:38.791 --> 16:40.666
Come on! Please be a good girl.

16:40.750 --> 16:42.833
[Norma Jeane] I am not an orphan!

16:43.666 --> 16:46.291
[woman] At least bring in
the suitcases, Clive, damn you!

16:46.375 --> 16:50.208
[Norma Jeane] My father
is coming back soon! He promised!

16:50.291 --> 16:51.833
[woman] No. Stop it!

16:51.916 --> 16:53.083
Stop crying! Stop!

16:53.166 --> 16:56.666
♪ Every baby needs a da-da-daddy ♪

16:56.750 --> 16:59.583
♪ To keep her worry free ♪

17:01.750 --> 17:05.750
♪ Every baby needs a da-da-daddy ♪

17:05.833 --> 17:09.958
♪ But where's one for me? ♪

17:10.041 --> 17:14.250
♪ Rich or poor, I don't care who ♪

17:14.333 --> 17:19.416
♪ If he hasn't got a million
Then a half will do ♪

17:19.500 --> 17:23.208
♪ Every baby needs a da-da-daddy ♪

17:23.291 --> 17:26.666
♪ Could my da-daddy be you? ♪

17:28.708 --> 17:31.458
[man] The circle of light is yours.

17:32.333 --> 17:35.291
It's a circle of light and attention.

17:39.333 --> 17:41.500
You enclose yourself in the circle.

17:44.583 --> 17:47.541
You carry it with you wherever you go.

17:48.458 --> 17:51.875
You're going to imagine
that next to your own real body,

17:51.958 --> 17:54.750
is the imaginary body of your character,

17:54.833 --> 17:56.625
whom you've created with your mind.

17:57.666 --> 18:01.333
♪ Every baby needs a da-da-daddy ♪

18:01.416 --> 18:05.458
♪ With silver in his hair… ♪

18:06.375 --> 18:09.791
Daddy, I couldn't imagine what to wear.

18:09.875 --> 18:11.625
You look fine.

18:12.250 --> 18:13.250
Are you sure?

18:14.000 --> 18:16.208
[sighs] I mean, I'm so jumpy.

18:16.291 --> 18:19.416
Just don't be late
for your appointment at 5:00.

18:19.500 --> 18:23.000
As if I would be late. My God.

18:25.375 --> 18:27.500
Don't you see, Norma Jeane?

18:27.583 --> 18:30.750
The future is in the palm of your hand.

18:32.000 --> 18:35.958
[Norma Jeane] Marilyn Monroe for Mr. Z?

18:43.083 --> 18:48.125
"Imagine, to know every night

18:48.208 --> 18:50.875
that differing hundreds of people
love you."

18:51.583 --> 18:52.875
"They want you."

18:53.916 --> 18:55.041
"You belong."

18:57.291 --> 18:59.750
"Just that alone is worth anything."

19:20.333 --> 19:21.583
[Mr. Z panting]

19:22.791 --> 19:24.833
"You carry it with you wherever you go."

19:25.791 --> 19:27.375
"The circle of light is yours."

19:27.458 --> 19:34.208
♪ Every baby needs a da-da-daddy
In case she runs aground ♪

19:35.916 --> 19:39.833
♪ Every baby needs a da-da-daddy ♪

19:39.916 --> 19:43.333
♪ To keep her safe and sound ♪

19:43.416 --> 19:47.958
♪ Yes, we feel just like Red Riding Hood ♪

19:48.041 --> 19:50.166
♪ 'Cause the wolves are awful hungry… ♪

19:50.250 --> 19:51.791
[man] You don't have to read.

19:52.916 --> 19:54.208
I don't understand.

19:55.166 --> 19:59.083
[man] You're in. You're cast.
If your name is Marilyn Monroe.

20:01.083 --> 20:02.333
Yes, that's me.

20:03.333 --> 20:05.291
[splutters] But I don't understand.

20:06.166 --> 20:09.791
Do you see that man?
That's Max Fabian, the producer.

20:09.875 --> 20:11.708
Now go and do yourself some good.

20:12.500 --> 20:15.083
Why do they always look
like unhappy rabbits?

20:15.166 --> 20:18.416
'Cause that's what they are.
Now go and make him happy.

20:18.500 --> 20:23.333
♪ Oh, every baby needs a da-da-daddy ♪

20:23.416 --> 20:26.916
♪ Could my da-daddy be you? ♪

20:27.833 --> 20:31.625
♪ Could my da-daddy be you? ♪

20:32.500 --> 20:34.250
[Norma Jeane screaming]

20:36.041 --> 20:39.125
[playwright] It's all right, Norma Jeane.
Come back, Norma Jeane.

20:39.208 --> 20:40.833
Come back here, Norma Jeane.

20:42.625 --> 20:43.833
[screaming continues]

20:46.375 --> 20:49.833
Hey. It's okay.

20:50.708 --> 20:51.708
[screams]

20:57.291 --> 20:58.250
[breathing heavily]

21:03.750 --> 21:04.708
It's okay.

21:18.000 --> 21:20.500
-[playwright] It's all right, Norma Jeane.
-[sighs]

21:20.583 --> 21:23.500
[playwright] Hey. Everything's all right.

21:24.625 --> 21:25.458
[exhales]

21:26.541 --> 21:31.041
[playwright] Norma Jeane?
What were you thinking of?

21:33.958 --> 21:35.250
I wasn't thinking.

21:36.416 --> 21:37.333
[chuckles softly]

21:40.458 --> 21:41.791
Um, maybe…

21:42.416 --> 21:43.583
[sighs, sniffles]

21:44.458 --> 21:47.083
…I was remembering?

21:48.291 --> 21:49.666
[bell buzzes]

21:54.166 --> 21:56.666
-[machine beeps]
-[bell rings]

22:00.250 --> 22:01.208
[sighs]

22:08.750 --> 22:12.291
I… I read the script, the whole script.

22:13.625 --> 22:18.916
It's, um…
such a strange, disturbing story.

22:20.125 --> 22:23.833
This mentally unbalanced woman
almost killing a little girl.

22:25.666 --> 22:29.291
Like a novel by Dostoyevsky,
where you feel sympathy for the criminal

22:30.125 --> 22:31.875
and don't wish to see her punished.

22:33.333 --> 22:36.416
[director] Oh, you've read Dostoyevsky,
have you, honey?

22:37.541 --> 22:39.708
[chuckles] All right.

22:42.625 --> 22:46.083
-[man coughs]
-[Norma Jeane clears throat]

22:46.166 --> 22:49.041
[director] Well, Miss Monroe,
let's, uh… let's begin.

23:02.583 --> 23:03.583
Miss Monroe?

23:04.166 --> 23:05.625
[breath trembling]

23:39.041 --> 23:42.041
You go back now. Go back.

23:43.083 --> 23:44.166
[man] "She yours?"

23:45.166 --> 23:48.500
No. She doesn't belong to me.

23:50.208 --> 23:53.916
This isn't your room.
You go back in there and go to sleep.

23:54.500 --> 23:55.833
[man] "She's crying."

23:57.666 --> 24:00.208
If you don't pay
any attention to them, they stop.

24:04.291 --> 24:08.541
"I think I'd better leave
before twins pop out of the closet."

24:14.250 --> 24:16.333
But you haven't any reason to leave now.

24:19.583 --> 24:21.500
"Sure, I have. I want to."

24:24.916 --> 24:26.125
I'll go with you.

24:27.541 --> 24:30.833
-Let's go dancing.
-[man] "What's the matter with you?"

24:31.791 --> 24:33.916
"You're supposed
to be here with that kid."

24:36.291 --> 24:37.291
Then stay.

24:39.291 --> 24:41.083
She won't bother you anymore.

24:42.416 --> 24:43.583
[man] "You bother me."

24:44.583 --> 24:45.958
"I can't figure you out."

24:54.833 --> 24:56.666
I'll be any way you want me to be.

24:57.958 --> 25:02.250
[man] "Why? Why is it so important?"

25:02.333 --> 25:03.625
Because…

25:05.916 --> 25:08.541
I belong with you, Philip.

25:12.958 --> 25:15.083
I didn't think you were ever coming back.

25:17.125 --> 25:18.250
"I'm Jed, Nell."

25:20.125 --> 25:21.791
"I'm not the man you think I am."

25:23.666 --> 25:24.500
"Remember?"

25:25.916 --> 25:27.166
"Remember Philip?"

25:33.125 --> 25:34.000
Yes.

25:36.416 --> 25:40.708
[man] "Now, think back."

25:45.375 --> 25:46.375
"Think."

25:49.583 --> 25:52.666
"What did he look like?"

25:59.500 --> 26:01.125
[Norma Jeane gasps] He had…

26:03.916 --> 26:05.041
brown eyes.

26:09.041 --> 26:10.750
Shiny black hair.

26:21.083 --> 26:24.750
"I'm not Philip. I'm Jed, Nell."

26:26.291 --> 26:27.750
"I'm Jed."

26:31.166 --> 26:32.666
People's names…

26:35.375 --> 26:36.666
You're not him.

26:41.666 --> 26:42.916
You never were.

26:55.166 --> 26:56.666
Thank you, Miss Monroe.

27:01.250 --> 27:02.125
[sniffles]

27:03.916 --> 27:04.750
[exhales]

27:06.666 --> 27:08.500
Please. [exhales]

27:09.541 --> 27:10.708
Can I try again?

27:12.333 --> 27:13.166
Oh…

27:16.125 --> 27:19.416
I… [exhales] I know I could be Nell.

27:20.916 --> 27:22.250
I think I am Nell.

27:23.416 --> 27:24.833
She's a sleepwalker.

27:25.625 --> 27:29.583
She doesn't see him.
She sees her dead fiancé.

27:29.666 --> 27:31.250
She's trapped in delusion.

27:33.041 --> 27:35.541
But where does dreaming end
and madness begin?

27:37.625 --> 27:41.791
Anyway, isn't all love based on delusion?

27:44.916 --> 27:47.916
[whispers] It was beautiful…
[continues indistinctly]

27:48.458 --> 27:51.875
-I really wanted…
-Thank you, John. Thank you, gentlemen.

27:51.958 --> 27:53.083
[man] That was, uh…

27:53.166 --> 27:54.541
We'll hear from you.

27:54.625 --> 27:56.000
[man] …pretty bad, wasn't it?

27:59.416 --> 28:00.458
Like, um,

28:02.166 --> 28:04.250
watching a mental patient, maybe.

28:05.041 --> 28:07.666
Not acting. No technique.

28:07.750 --> 28:11.000
People like that, you can see
why they're drawn to acting.

28:11.083 --> 28:13.875
Because the actor in her role
always knows who she is.

28:14.791 --> 28:15.958
What do you think, boss?

28:16.458 --> 28:17.833
[director coughing]

28:20.833 --> 28:21.791
Sweet Jesus.

28:23.458 --> 28:25.166
Look at the ass on that little girl.

28:45.083 --> 28:47.791
[Norma Jeane] Are you sure a visit
with her won't be too upsetting?

28:48.958 --> 28:52.208
[doctor] Upsetting to your mother
or to you, Miss Baker?

28:58.000 --> 29:00.250
I haven't seen my mother in ten years.

29:02.416 --> 29:03.916
[patients shouting]

29:15.625 --> 29:17.833
Those are some
of our more troubled patients.

29:21.208 --> 29:22.416
Here we are.

29:40.041 --> 29:41.250
Oh, Mother.

29:48.750 --> 29:50.125
[sobbing]

30:20.416 --> 30:21.500
Mother?

30:25.833 --> 30:29.458
Mother, it's me. It's me, Norma Jeane.

30:37.291 --> 30:38.916
[sniffles, exhales tearfully]

31:17.583 --> 31:19.500
Mother, it's so nice here.

31:25.000 --> 31:26.375
Isn't it nice here?

31:46.000 --> 31:47.291
Are you warmer now?

31:49.625 --> 31:52.166
Oh, this shawl, it's so pretty on you.

32:13.375 --> 32:16.125
It's been so exciting this past year.

32:17.250 --> 32:20.291
So wonderful. Like a fairy tale.

32:22.666 --> 32:24.416
Sometimes, I can't believe it.

32:32.208 --> 32:34.458
I'm under contract at the studio.

32:35.250 --> 32:36.750
Where you used to work.

32:38.375 --> 32:40.875
I can make a living
just being photographed.

32:57.458 --> 33:00.083
I guess there isn't
any Norma Jeane, is there?

33:11.833 --> 33:12.666
Mother?

33:19.250 --> 33:22.500
My father was under contract
to the studio, you said.

33:24.750 --> 33:26.750
Around 1925?

33:31.875 --> 33:35.750
I've been sneaking around there
trying to find his picture in the files--

33:35.833 --> 33:37.166
[mother] Where's my daughter?

33:38.208 --> 33:40.000
They said my daughter was coming.

33:41.291 --> 33:42.708
I don't know you. Who are you?

34:54.625 --> 34:56.208
[director] And cut.

34:58.833 --> 35:03.166
[mother] Yes, cut. Don't be a coward. Cut.

35:03.250 --> 35:04.291
Do it!

35:11.583 --> 35:13.083
[indistinct chatter]

35:21.791 --> 35:22.833
[man] You all right?

35:25.250 --> 35:26.208
Hey.

35:27.708 --> 35:29.583
Hey, what's wrong? You okay?

35:33.000 --> 35:36.500
Dee-Dee, it's okay. I have it.
We're fine, thank you.

35:38.250 --> 35:40.041
-[Norma Jeane cries]
-[man] Oh, dear.

35:42.250 --> 35:44.916
Hey, that's all right.
Everything is okay. Thank you.

35:45.750 --> 35:46.750
Give us a second.

35:49.208 --> 35:50.541
[breathing heavily]

35:50.625 --> 35:53.875
[announcer] Marilyn Monroe,
a rising new Hollywood talent

35:53.958 --> 35:57.916
proves herself a strong dynamic presence
in this darkly disturbing thriller.

35:58.000 --> 35:59.833
Also starring Richard Widmark.

35:59.916 --> 36:03.875
Her portrayal
of a mentally unbalanced young babysitter

36:03.958 --> 36:05.416
is so chillingly convincing--

36:05.500 --> 36:10.875
Mr. Shinn, at the premiere,
I shut my eyes a lot.

36:12.083 --> 36:14.500
I couldn't believe that girl was me.

36:15.250 --> 36:18.833
But everyone in the audience
would think it was me, Nell.

36:20.583 --> 36:23.958
And later at the party, Marilyn.

36:25.666 --> 36:27.708
[Shinn over telephone]
Are you on painkillers?

36:28.708 --> 36:30.000
Is it your period?

36:31.958 --> 36:32.791
Oh.

36:33.291 --> 36:34.916
No. No, it's not.

36:36.166 --> 36:38.000
Um, what business of yours--

36:38.083 --> 36:41.708
[Shinn] Sweetheart, the next film
is going to be terrific, I promise you.

36:41.791 --> 36:44.166
A whole lot classier than Don't Bother,

36:44.250 --> 36:47.958
which I think is a stagy piece of crap
except for you, but don't quote me.

36:50.708 --> 36:54.708
["Für Elise" playing on piano]

37:38.083 --> 37:40.708
["Für Elise" ends]

37:43.833 --> 37:46.833
[ethereal melody playing on piano]

38:13.708 --> 38:15.833
[man 1] Marilyn deserves better than this.

38:18.416 --> 38:20.166
Marilyn is gonna be a star.

38:22.375 --> 38:23.458
[sniffs]

38:26.416 --> 38:27.666
This place…

38:28.958 --> 38:30.375
Know what it smells of?

38:31.833 --> 38:34.500
Dreary old love-paste.

38:35.750 --> 38:39.333
Nothing more dreary
than rancid old love-paste.

38:43.333 --> 38:45.708
You know, we've performed in porn films.

38:47.250 --> 38:49.625
Just for the hell of it. Not for cash.

38:50.250 --> 38:53.416
I didn't sneer at the cash. I never do.

38:57.333 --> 38:59.916
-[man 2 chuckles]
-She's a prude.

39:01.375 --> 39:03.708
Miss Golden Dreams of all people.

39:04.625 --> 39:05.583
[pills rattle]

39:12.333 --> 39:14.916
The human body is meant to be seen.

39:22.041 --> 39:23.625
Admired and…

39:25.625 --> 39:26.583
desired.

39:32.250 --> 39:37.166
Not hidden away
like some ugly festering wound.

39:38.208 --> 39:40.750
[man 1] There's plenty of bodies
that should be hidden away.

39:40.833 --> 39:43.333
But not yours, Cassie, and not mine.

39:44.208 --> 39:45.916
And for sure not our girl Norma's.

39:48.791 --> 39:50.208
What are you doing?

39:52.000 --> 39:53.416
Are you looking at her?

39:58.166 --> 39:59.375
Can you see her?

40:02.666 --> 40:04.750
I like to watch myself in the mirror.

40:06.666 --> 40:09.083
I like to watch myself on the toilet even.

40:12.250 --> 40:16.208
In our household, my father, Chaplin,

40:17.333 --> 40:18.791
was all the magic.

40:20.333 --> 40:22.208
He drew all the light into himself

40:22.291 --> 40:25.041
until there was
nothing left inside me but numbness.

40:26.250 --> 40:27.250
Like sleep.

40:28.958 --> 40:31.291
Only in the mirror could I see myself.

40:33.125 --> 40:34.750
Anything I did in the mirror,

40:36.250 --> 40:40.125
I could hear waves and waves of applause.

40:40.208 --> 40:43.000
[ethereal music playing]

40:45.500 --> 40:46.708
Look, Norma Jeane.

40:51.625 --> 40:52.833
There she is.

40:54.833 --> 40:56.041
Your magic friend.

42:03.791 --> 42:05.541
[Cass] Were you waiting for us?

42:08.666 --> 42:09.791
Norma?

42:13.416 --> 42:14.250
Yes.

42:16.083 --> 42:17.416
Were you starved for us?

42:19.291 --> 42:20.291
Yes.

42:22.250 --> 42:24.416
But don't be nice to us.

42:26.708 --> 42:29.166
[man 1] Yeah. Like feeding a cobra.

42:29.875 --> 42:32.208
I'd use a ten-foot stick on me, myself.

42:35.833 --> 42:36.833
[moaning]

42:40.208 --> 42:42.833
♪ Take me, take me ♪

42:42.916 --> 42:45.416
♪ Thrill me, thrill me ♪

42:45.500 --> 42:48.791
♪ Take me ♪

42:48.875 --> 42:53.375
♪ This is the moment
Oh, thrill me ♪

43:05.416 --> 43:10.041
♪ Take me, take me in your arms… ♪

43:10.583 --> 43:13.625
[announcer] She sang of love
just as she lived for love.

43:13.708 --> 43:17.958
Like a Lorelei, flaunting her charms
as she lured men on and on

43:18.041 --> 43:19.875
to their eternal destruction.

43:21.208 --> 43:24.833
It's Marilyn Monroe,
skyrocketing to new dramatic heights.

43:24.916 --> 43:27.541
When a man
took her loveliness in his arms,

43:27.625 --> 43:28.916
he took his life in his hands.

43:29.000 --> 43:31.625
You smell like a dime store.
I know what that means.

43:31.708 --> 43:33.833
Sure, I'm meeting somebody.

43:33.916 --> 43:36.458
Just anybody handy, as long as he's a man.

43:36.541 --> 43:39.250
[announcer] Joseph Cotten,
helpless in her siren spell.

43:39.333 --> 43:40.583
That is not our Norma.

43:41.958 --> 43:43.875
That's not our little Fishie.

43:43.958 --> 43:47.916
[announcer] But she could never be his
nor any man's completely.

43:48.000 --> 43:49.875
And that thought whipped him into a frenzy

43:49.958 --> 43:53.333
that makes the screen thunder
with unparalleled suspense.

43:53.416 --> 43:54.250
[cries out]

43:54.333 --> 43:56.333
[moans]

43:56.416 --> 43:58.833
[dramatic music playing]

44:06.500 --> 44:08.833
[breathing heavily]

44:22.916 --> 44:24.916
[Norma Jeane] She is pretty, I guess.

44:25.000 --> 44:27.625
But it isn't me, is it?

44:36.916 --> 44:38.625
How about when people find out?

44:39.500 --> 44:42.333
Hell, baby, we found out,
and we still love you.

44:46.791 --> 44:49.916
I just… I wish
I could just hide in your arms.

44:50.875 --> 44:52.916
Forever and ever in your arms.

44:54.583 --> 44:56.291
But you don't mean that, Norma.

44:57.250 --> 44:59.041
An actress wants to be seen.

45:00.541 --> 45:04.166
An actress wants to be loved
by a multitude of people.

45:04.250 --> 45:07.791
No. What I really want is you.

45:10.791 --> 45:12.000
[Cass] You're so sweet.

45:14.083 --> 45:16.708
I hate this one. I look like an asshole.

45:17.708 --> 45:20.083
With my mouth open, like I'm panting.

45:21.083 --> 45:22.708
[panting]

45:23.666 --> 45:24.958
[chuckles]

45:25.875 --> 45:28.958
"Young men-about-town, Charlie Chaplin Jr.

45:29.583 --> 45:32.166
and Edward G. Robinson Jr."

45:34.000 --> 45:37.666
"And blonde sexpot, Marilyn Monroe."

45:38.166 --> 45:39.083
"A threesome."

45:39.166 --> 45:40.500
[Eddy chuckles]

45:40.583 --> 45:41.833
How vulgar.

45:44.000 --> 45:45.208
"A sexpot."

45:46.875 --> 45:48.416
What is a "sexpot"?

45:49.666 --> 45:54.000
Is this the sexpot?

45:54.083 --> 45:54.958
[chuckles]

45:55.041 --> 45:56.250
-No!
-Or this?

45:56.333 --> 45:58.875
[shrieks] No! No!

45:58.958 --> 46:01.291
[shouting indistinctly]

46:02.416 --> 46:04.958
No! [laughing]

46:07.458 --> 46:10.208
I don't want you seen
in public with them, Norma Jeane.

46:15.125 --> 46:16.416
And in private?

46:20.125 --> 46:21.375
In private…

46:24.333 --> 46:25.791
take precautions.

46:25.875 --> 46:27.833
Oh, Mr. Shinn, that's so cruel.

46:28.791 --> 46:31.916
It's crude and cruel.
And you… you know it.

46:32.666 --> 46:36.833
I'm just thinking of your career
and your well-being.

46:38.666 --> 46:40.041
You're thinking of Marilyn.

46:40.791 --> 46:42.625
-[Shinn] Yes.
-Her career.

46:42.708 --> 46:46.125
Yes. And her well-being.

46:46.750 --> 46:48.583
She doesn't have any well-being.

46:50.333 --> 46:51.666
She's only a career.

46:55.625 --> 46:57.125
They know I'm Norma.

46:58.125 --> 46:59.208
Not Marilyn.

47:01.875 --> 47:03.500
They understand me.

47:05.041 --> 47:08.625
I understand you. I invented you.

47:13.541 --> 47:14.416
[chuckles]

47:16.500 --> 47:18.125
[Cass] Oh, Norma.

47:20.875 --> 47:22.375
I guess I do love you.

47:24.791 --> 47:26.333
I'm jealous of you and Eddy.

47:28.708 --> 47:30.666
Jealous of anybody who looks at you.

47:33.958 --> 47:36.375
If I could love any woman,

47:37.833 --> 47:38.875
it'd be you.

47:41.791 --> 47:43.250
When you say you love me

47:44.958 --> 47:46.208
and when you look at me…

47:49.291 --> 47:52.750
who do you see, truly?

47:53.541 --> 47:55.541
The Little Tramp? Do you see him?

47:56.458 --> 47:57.416
No.

47:58.958 --> 48:00.250
I see only you.

48:05.333 --> 48:09.708
People think it's a blessing
being Charlie Chaplin's son.

48:11.333 --> 48:14.750
Like it's a fairy tale,
and I'm the king's son.

48:15.916 --> 48:17.541
But we're cursed, Eddy and me.

48:21.083 --> 48:24.208
We're juniors… of men who never wanted us.

48:29.416 --> 48:31.541
But at least you two have fathers.

48:32.916 --> 48:34.541
At least you know who you are.

48:36.791 --> 48:40.166
[smacks lips] Oh, we knew
who we were before we were born.

48:42.083 --> 48:43.583
You never knew your father.

48:44.666 --> 48:45.875
So you're free.

48:47.125 --> 48:48.416
You can invent yourself.

48:50.708 --> 48:52.208
I love your name.

48:52.833 --> 48:55.125
-Marilyn Monroe.
-[Eddy] Mm-hmm.

48:55.916 --> 48:58.458
[chuckling] It's so totally phony.

48:58.541 --> 49:00.083
-[Eddy laughs]
-I love it.

49:02.666 --> 49:05.083
Like you gave birth to yourself.

49:07.416 --> 49:09.125
[Norma Jeane] Because of his eyes.

49:09.625 --> 49:11.750
He had the most beautiful eyes.

49:12.750 --> 49:15.208
Because he'd gazed upon me
with those eyes.

49:16.041 --> 49:18.375
Haunting, soulful eyes.

49:18.458 --> 49:20.958
From a wall
of Mother's long-ago apartment.

49:23.208 --> 49:25.666
Because he would say, seeing me…

49:26.583 --> 49:28.750
I knew you as soon as I saw you.

49:31.833 --> 49:33.083
Fatherless.

49:34.708 --> 49:35.833
Like me.

49:38.000 --> 49:39.833
And then your mother abandoned…

49:42.250 --> 49:43.458
and debased.

49:44.166 --> 49:45.291
Like mine.

49:47.000 --> 49:49.916
[Norma Jeane] Because he would love me
as other men would not.

49:51.875 --> 49:52.958
Or could not.

49:54.083 --> 49:55.333
As a twin.

49:56.250 --> 49:57.666
With his soul.

49:57.750 --> 49:58.958
There's Gemini.

50:00.166 --> 50:01.166
See?

50:03.083 --> 50:04.750
Both Norma and I are Geminis.

50:06.416 --> 50:07.875
The fated twins.

50:12.083 --> 50:13.083
Where?

50:13.958 --> 50:17.083
-I don't see it. Where?
-There.

50:22.166 --> 50:24.125
It's all billions of years old.

50:25.583 --> 50:27.208
Unimaginably vast.

50:28.625 --> 50:30.041
Yet it began out of what?

50:32.041 --> 50:35.083
Particles so small
it couldn't be seen by the human eye.

50:36.833 --> 50:39.708
[Norma Jeane] Look at them up there,
shining so brightly.

50:42.083 --> 50:44.458
And yet, each one is so very much alone.

50:46.958 --> 50:48.250
I'll drink to that.

50:53.958 --> 50:57.000
Let's vow, okay? The three of us.

50:58.291 --> 51:01.291
To always love each other like right now.

51:02.166 --> 51:04.291
And to die for each other, if needed.

51:06.666 --> 51:07.875
We're a triangle.

51:09.458 --> 51:12.333
A triangle can't be divided in two,
like two can be.

51:13.875 --> 51:17.541
We're the Gemini, the three of us.

51:17.625 --> 51:20.458
Like twins. But there's three.

51:20.541 --> 51:21.875
[chuckles]

51:21.958 --> 51:22.958
[laughs]

51:28.000 --> 51:29.208
To the Gemini.

51:33.541 --> 51:34.750
To the Gemini.

51:36.458 --> 51:39.000
[ethereal music playing]

52:07.500 --> 52:08.333
[sobs]

52:12.208 --> 52:14.541
Oh God, I knew.

52:16.958 --> 52:21.750
I guess I knew.
I've been feeling so swollen and so happy.

52:21.833 --> 52:23.333
[laughing]

52:23.416 --> 52:25.291
[doctor] My dear, you're healthy.

52:27.041 --> 52:28.625
Everything's gonna be fine.

52:31.291 --> 52:33.041
I'm happy, I said.

52:34.250 --> 52:36.375
I want this baby.

52:36.458 --> 52:40.208
My husband and I have been trying
for years. [clears throat]

52:40.916 --> 52:41.791
[laughs]

52:46.541 --> 52:47.958
[panting]

52:50.500 --> 52:51.500
[chuckling] Hey, Norma.

52:55.041 --> 52:59.125
What is it? You look… fraught. And happy.

52:59.208 --> 53:00.583
[Norma Jeane exclaims]

53:06.541 --> 53:07.625
Oh, Norma…

53:09.791 --> 53:10.916
You think you are?

53:15.291 --> 53:17.375
-Is this what I think it is?
-Yes!

53:18.458 --> 53:20.291
[Eddy laughing] Oh, man!

53:24.083 --> 53:25.458
Are you happy for me?

53:27.416 --> 53:30.041
Us? The Gemini, I mean?

53:34.041 --> 53:35.541
-Yes!
-Yes!

53:35.625 --> 53:37.625
[Cass and Norma Jeane chuckling]

53:45.208 --> 53:46.541
It's like the movies.

53:48.000 --> 53:50.666
The kind of thing that only happens
in the movies.

53:50.750 --> 53:51.625
What?

53:54.416 --> 53:56.083
[Norma Jeane] That little tiger.

53:56.166 --> 53:58.291
[chuckles] Oh!

54:01.291 --> 54:02.208
[sigh

54:03.333 --> 54:04.791
I had one like him once.

54:06.000 --> 54:08.208
A long time ago when I was a little girl.

54:09.750 --> 54:11.208
Baby's first plaything.

54:12.916 --> 54:13.750
Cute.

54:16.500 --> 54:19.500
Cass, where are you taking us?

54:21.000 --> 54:22.333
I wanna go home.

54:23.916 --> 54:24.916
Right?

54:26.250 --> 54:27.750
Baby's so sleepy.

54:30.250 --> 54:32.916
Oh, this is a vision for baby to see.

54:34.541 --> 54:35.541
Just wait.

54:44.416 --> 54:47.833
Norma, you can look or not,

54:49.083 --> 54:52.958
but… there she is.

54:54.916 --> 54:56.500
Mmm… Marilyn.

54:56.583 --> 54:57.500
Marilyn.

55:08.708 --> 55:10.541
[Norma Jeane] I can't take the role.

55:11.208 --> 55:12.500
I'm sorry.

55:16.000 --> 55:17.875
[Shinn over telephone]
Are you still on the line?

55:19.125 --> 55:20.333
Is something wrong?

55:21.000 --> 55:22.833
[Norma Jeane] No, nothing's wrong.

55:23.333 --> 55:24.625
I just can't.

55:25.625 --> 55:26.458
Not now.

55:27.250 --> 55:30.791
[Shinn] Not now? Why not now?

55:33.291 --> 55:37.000
You're the newest
box office sensation now.

55:37.875 --> 55:42.958
Zanuck has bought
Gentlemen Prefer Blondes for you.

55:43.041 --> 55:46.666
He wants it as a showcase for you.

55:50.458 --> 55:51.750
How much would I get?

55:56.708 --> 55:58.291
[Shinn] Your contract salary.

55:59.541 --> 56:00.791
Five hundred a week.

56:05.208 --> 56:07.291
How much would Jane Russell get?

56:09.208 --> 56:10.750
[Shinn] The deal is pending.

56:11.250 --> 56:13.500
And Russell has to be lent
by another studio.

56:16.375 --> 56:17.875
Yes, but how much?

56:18.541 --> 56:20.916
[Shinn scoffs] The figures
aren't finalized.

56:21.000 --> 56:21.916
How much?

56:24.583 --> 56:29.166
[Shinn] They're asking… $100,000.

56:32.416 --> 56:34.083
$100,000?

56:39.125 --> 56:43.416
I'll get about $5,000,
and Jane Russell gets $100,000?

56:44.041 --> 56:48.500
And I'm playing the blonde
in Gentlemen Prefer Blondes?

56:50.375 --> 56:51.625
That's an insult.

56:53.458 --> 56:56.958
-I'm gonna hang up now. Goodbye.
-[Shinn] Marilyn, wait.

56:57.041 --> 56:59.208
Fuck Marilyn. She's not here.

57:11.708 --> 57:12.708
[chuckles softly]

57:26.875 --> 57:28.208
"To My Baby."

57:30.416 --> 57:31.416
In you

57:32.916 --> 57:38.291
The world is born anew

57:40.958 --> 57:42.166
Before you

57:44.166 --> 57:47.333
There was none

57:49.875 --> 57:51.958
How'd you like to be a grandmother?

57:54.375 --> 57:55.708
[Mother] What year is it?

57:56.833 --> 57:58.458
What time did we travel to?

58:01.375 --> 58:03.916
Mother, it's May 1953.

58:06.125 --> 58:07.333
I'm Norma Jeane.

58:08.375 --> 58:10.000
I'm here to take care of you.

58:12.291 --> 58:13.708
But your hair is so white.

58:14.625 --> 58:16.166
[Norma Jeane chuckles softly]

58:24.500 --> 58:28.333
When you had me, Mother,
you weren't married, I guess.

58:29.291 --> 58:31.708
You didn't have a man supporting you.

58:33.500 --> 58:34.916
And you had a baby.

58:45.666 --> 58:46.958
That was so brave.

58:50.416 --> 58:51.833
Another girl would've…

58:54.750 --> 58:58.083
well, you know, gotten rid of it.

58:59.833 --> 59:00.791
Of me.

59:03.958 --> 59:08.333
And I wouldn't be here at all.
There wouldn't be any Marilyn.

59:11.000 --> 59:13.250
And she's getting so famous now.

59:15.458 --> 59:17.625
Fan letters, telegrams.

59:19.208 --> 59:20.791
Flowers from strangers.

59:36.750 --> 59:38.125
But you were brave.

59:44.291 --> 59:45.916
You did the right thing.

59:49.625 --> 59:51.000
You had your baby.

59:56.041 --> 59:57.041
You had me.

1:00:01.708 --> 1:00:03.875
[doctor] Hers is a mystery illness.

1:00:09.000 --> 1:00:10.958
An illness no one truly understands.

1:00:12.833 --> 1:00:14.166
A syndrome of symptoms.

1:00:22.708 --> 1:00:24.125
Is it inherited?

1:00:25.458 --> 1:00:26.541
[doctor] Excuse me?

1:00:30.500 --> 1:00:33.625
My mother's illness, are you…

1:00:36.291 --> 1:00:37.500
Are you…

1:00:38.666 --> 1:00:40.625
Are you born with it in your blood?

1:00:47.333 --> 1:00:49.500
[line ringing]

1:01:04.208 --> 1:01:05.416
[line picks up]

1:01:05.500 --> 1:01:09.041
[Mr. Z] All right, Marilyn, what I'll do
is I'll turn you over to Yvet.

1:01:09.125 --> 1:01:11.916
You remember Yvet? She'll help you.

1:01:12.000 --> 1:01:13.416
[Yvet] Marilyn?

1:01:13.500 --> 1:01:14.666
[crying]

1:01:15.916 --> 1:01:20.916
-I need help. I need help so badly.
-[Yvet] Dear, I'll make the arrangements.

1:01:21.000 --> 1:01:24.291
Plan on tomorrow morning at 8:00 a.m.
You'll be picked up at home.

1:02:18.833 --> 1:02:21.041
[dramatic piano music playing]

1:02:21.125 --> 1:02:22.458
Please, I wanna go back.

1:02:29.375 --> 1:02:32.208
-[knocking on glass]
-Hey, I've changed my mind.

1:02:33.666 --> 1:02:35.166
My mind's my own to change.

1:02:40.208 --> 1:02:41.750
Oh, the bright lights.

1:02:49.375 --> 1:02:50.583
[breathing heavily]

1:02:52.458 --> 1:02:54.416
[woman] You're in good hands, dear.

1:02:57.708 --> 1:03:01.375
Please, won't you listen?
I've changed my mind.

1:03:10.291 --> 1:03:12.208
Please, don't. Won't you listen?

1:03:15.458 --> 1:03:18.375
[doctor] This will put you
in twilight sleep.

1:03:19.833 --> 1:03:22.041
No, I… wanna go back.

1:03:23.666 --> 1:03:25.500
[breathing heavily]

1:03:39.625 --> 1:03:42.166
No. Wait.

1:03:42.750 --> 1:03:45.583
Wait! Wait! No! No!

1:03:51.458 --> 1:03:52.291
No!

1:04:16.625 --> 1:04:18.125
[baby crying]

1:04:49.500 --> 1:04:50.541
[knock on door]

1:04:53.583 --> 1:04:55.125
[knocking continues]

1:04:59.666 --> 1:05:00.791
[crew member] Miss Monroe?

1:05:03.500 --> 1:05:07.750
♪ Bye-bye, baby ♪

1:05:07.833 --> 1:05:09.041
[knocking continues]

1:05:09.125 --> 1:05:13.041
♪ Remember you're my baby… ♪

1:05:13.125 --> 1:05:13.958
Miss Monroe.

1:05:17.125 --> 1:05:18.916
Miss Monroe, it's time.

1:05:26.166 --> 1:05:30.083
♪ I'll be lonely… ♪

1:05:31.208 --> 1:05:32.916
[knocking continues]

1:05:33.000 --> 1:05:34.291
[crew member] Miss Monroe?

1:05:37.833 --> 1:05:44.750
♪ There'll be no other guy ♪

1:05:45.583 --> 1:05:48.208
[man] I'm one of the winners
of the American lottery.

1:05:48.708 --> 1:05:50.958
I know it. I'm grateful for it.

1:05:52.041 --> 1:05:55.541
And I never take it for granted.
Baseball was my life.

1:05:56.416 --> 1:05:58.416
Baseball was my ticket up and out.

1:05:58.500 --> 1:06:00.250
And now, well,

1:06:01.333 --> 1:06:02.291
I'm retired.

1:06:03.083 --> 1:06:08.208
I mean, I have plenty to do, you know,
endorsements and… personal appearances,

1:06:08.291 --> 1:06:09.916
advisory board meetings.

1:06:14.500 --> 1:06:16.166
I guess I sound like a sap.

1:06:16.791 --> 1:06:19.333
No. No. [chuckles] No, no.

1:06:20.583 --> 1:06:23.083
It must be awfully strange to be a…

1:06:24.416 --> 1:06:28.541
well… a hero.

1:06:31.916 --> 1:06:32.750
[chuckles]

1:06:33.666 --> 1:06:35.541
Anyway, you don't seem retired.

1:06:36.708 --> 1:06:38.916
You're in the paper so much.

1:06:39.708 --> 1:06:42.916
Well, not half as much as you, Marilyn.

1:06:45.041 --> 1:06:46.041
Who, me?

1:06:47.916 --> 1:06:48.916
Well…

1:06:51.125 --> 1:06:53.166
That's just studio publicity.

1:06:56.125 --> 1:06:57.375
Oh, they're awful.

1:06:59.791 --> 1:07:01.291
The things they make up.

1:07:03.333 --> 1:07:05.458
I know you're supposed to get used to it.

1:07:07.291 --> 1:07:08.291
[sighs]

1:07:08.375 --> 1:07:09.708
But I just can't.

1:07:11.750 --> 1:07:13.041
It really hurts.

1:07:21.541 --> 1:07:23.291
How'd you get your start?

1:07:37.083 --> 1:07:38.083
What start?

1:07:38.875 --> 1:07:40.041
In movies.

1:07:41.166 --> 1:07:42.125
In acting.

1:07:49.833 --> 1:07:52.375
[sighs] I don't know. [chuckles nervously]

1:07:57.250 --> 1:07:58.083
I…

1:07:59.166 --> 1:08:00.375
I… I guess…

1:08:05.375 --> 1:08:06.250
[exhales sharply]

1:08:10.625 --> 1:08:12.208
I guess I was discovered.

1:08:15.000 --> 1:08:16.833
-Oh, discovered. How?
-[Norma Jeane inhales]

1:08:16.916 --> 1:08:18.083
[flash bulb clicks]

1:08:20.083 --> 1:08:21.000
[gasps]

1:08:28.541 --> 1:08:30.041
Maybe we should leave.

1:08:33.083 --> 1:08:35.125
I'm afraid of some of the people here.

1:08:42.833 --> 1:08:43.833
Hey.

1:08:46.750 --> 1:08:48.291
I know what it's like…

1:08:51.166 --> 1:08:52.375
to be lonely…

1:08:54.916 --> 1:08:56.333
to want a better life.

1:08:58.083 --> 1:08:59.791
A good, simple life.

1:09:01.500 --> 1:09:03.166
A decent life.

1:09:09.833 --> 1:09:10.666
[sighs]

1:09:11.625 --> 1:09:13.791
I just wanna begin again from zero.

1:09:16.166 --> 1:09:17.416
I wanna live in…

1:09:18.750 --> 1:09:22.791
I wanna live in another world.
Away from Hollywood.

1:09:24.291 --> 1:09:25.708
I wanna live in…

1:09:27.500 --> 1:09:28.541
[sighs]

1:09:29.458 --> 1:09:30.625
…Chekhov!

1:09:34.500 --> 1:09:36.291
I wanna move to New York.

1:09:39.791 --> 1:09:41.083
And study acting.

1:09:42.916 --> 1:09:44.625
Serious acting.

1:09:44.708 --> 1:09:47.291
In the movies, they chop you all to bits.

1:09:47.375 --> 1:09:50.708
Cut, cut, cut. It's a jigsaw puzzle.

1:09:50.791 --> 1:09:53.000
But you're not the one
to put the pieces together.

1:09:55.208 --> 1:09:57.458
Oh, but to live in a part.

1:09:57.541 --> 1:10:01.416
To just be in it
till the closing curtain every night.

1:10:17.041 --> 1:10:18.458
But mostly, I…

1:10:23.375 --> 1:10:24.791
I wanna settle down.

1:10:26.666 --> 1:10:27.916
Like any girl.

1:10:28.958 --> 1:10:30.375
And have a family.

1:10:31.750 --> 1:10:32.708
[laughs]

1:10:33.750 --> 1:10:35.791
Oh, I love children so.

1:10:37.458 --> 1:10:39.458
I'm crazy about babies.

1:10:41.208 --> 1:10:42.291
[chuckles]

1:10:45.375 --> 1:10:47.000
[Norma Jeane] Did somebody die?

1:10:50.291 --> 1:10:51.500
What is all this?

1:10:53.583 --> 1:10:54.916
These flowers.

1:10:56.416 --> 1:10:57.666
[chuckles]

1:10:58.291 --> 1:10:59.500
Am I a corpse?

1:11:00.333 --> 1:11:01.833
Is this a funeral home?

1:11:01.916 --> 1:11:03.291
[all chuckling]

1:11:05.166 --> 1:11:07.833
[Norma Jeane] I'm a slave
to this Marilyn Monroe.

1:11:08.750 --> 1:11:11.291
I signed up for a luxury cruise,

1:11:11.375 --> 1:11:14.583
but like Lorelei Lee,
I'm in fucking steerage, paddling.

1:11:14.666 --> 1:11:15.875
[all laughing]

1:11:17.333 --> 1:11:20.750
[woman] Now, Miss Monroe,
you don't mean a word of what you say.

1:11:21.666 --> 1:11:23.833
If you weren't Marilyn, who'd you be?

1:11:24.875 --> 1:11:26.333
Miss Monroe, you're cruel.

1:11:27.458 --> 1:11:30.416
Every one of us, everybody in the world,

1:11:30.500 --> 1:11:33.750
would give their right arm
to be you, and you know it.

1:11:37.125 --> 1:11:38.041
Oh, I do.

1:11:39.958 --> 1:11:45.125
"Marilyn, you are the sweetheart of this
and any other month."

1:11:45.208 --> 1:11:46.208
[man] Aw.

1:11:46.708 --> 1:11:50.166
"Marilyn, you are a whore,
a blonde tramp."

1:11:50.250 --> 1:11:54.791
"Nobody will ever love you,
you disgusting tramp."

1:11:54.875 --> 1:12:00.333
"Get off our radio, television,
and out of our movies."

1:12:00.416 --> 1:12:02.083
"You're poisoning our children."

1:12:02.833 --> 1:12:03.833
"Not a fan."

1:12:07.750 --> 1:12:09.416
Like movie critics.

1:12:10.625 --> 1:12:13.666
Some of them love Marilyn,
some of them hate Marilyn.

1:12:15.875 --> 1:12:17.500
What's that got to do with me?

1:12:18.416 --> 1:12:19.416
Yes.

1:12:19.500 --> 1:12:21.666
♪ She is the whore of the month ♪

1:12:21.750 --> 1:12:24.541
-Whitey!
-♪ She's a sweet little tramp ♪ [laughing]

1:12:24.625 --> 1:12:27.208
♪ I'm gonna write me a letter
And stick on a stamp ♪

1:12:28.791 --> 1:12:32.583
Miss Monroe,
this is a confidential letter, I think.

1:12:35.458 --> 1:12:38.166
He's got a bat for a cock. Sorry.

1:12:38.250 --> 1:12:39.250
[laughs]

1:12:42.916 --> 1:12:44.708
[sighs] "Dear Norma Jeane."

1:12:45.708 --> 1:12:49.208
"This is possibly the most
difficult letter I have ever penned."

1:12:49.875 --> 1:12:53.166
[male voice] Honestly, I… I do not know
why I'm contacting you now

1:12:53.250 --> 1:12:55.250
after so many years.

1:12:55.333 --> 1:12:58.375
The truth is,
I have suffered a heart attack,

1:12:58.458 --> 1:13:01.083
and I have contemplated my life
with gravity.

1:13:01.833 --> 1:13:05.416
I cannot say I am proud of my behavior
in all cases.

1:13:06.083 --> 1:13:07.375
Oh, it's him.

1:13:07.916 --> 1:13:10.541
[male voice] I am your father,
Norma Jeane.

1:13:12.291 --> 1:13:14.166
And I have here before me

1:13:14.250 --> 1:13:19.083
an interview with Marilyn Monroe
in the new Pageant.

1:13:20.041 --> 1:13:22.083
Reading it, it brought tears to my eyes

1:13:23.166 --> 1:13:25.541
when you said
that your mother has been hospitalized,

1:13:25.625 --> 1:13:27.458
and you do not know your father.

1:13:28.875 --> 1:13:31.916
Although you await him
with every passing hour.

1:13:33.333 --> 1:13:34.791
Oh, my poor daughter.

1:13:36.166 --> 1:13:37.416
Oh God.

1:13:38.416 --> 1:13:40.708
-[father] I did not know.
-Oh, it's him.

1:13:41.583 --> 1:13:43.958
[breathing heavily] I knew.

1:13:45.333 --> 1:13:47.958
[exhales sharply]
Watching over me all these years.

1:13:49.583 --> 1:13:50.708
I felt it.

1:13:52.125 --> 1:13:55.791
[father] I will contact you again soon,
Norma Jeane, in person.

1:13:55.875 --> 1:13:57.000
[chuckles]

1:13:57.083 --> 1:13:59.958
[father] So look for me,
my precious daughter,

1:14:01.791 --> 1:14:03.750
upon a special occasion in your life

1:14:04.708 --> 1:14:08.625
where both father and daughter
can celebrate our long-denied love.

1:14:10.708 --> 1:14:11.708
Your tearful father.

1:14:12.958 --> 1:14:15.750
[crowd chanting]
Marilyn! Marilyn! Marilyn!

1:14:15.833 --> 1:14:19.791
Marilyn! Marilyn! Marilyn! Marilyn!

1:14:19.875 --> 1:14:24.083
Marilyn! Marilyn! Marilyn! Marilyn!

1:14:24.166 --> 1:14:25.500
[cheering]

1:14:30.000 --> 1:14:32.125
[chanting continues] Marilyn! Marilyn!

1:14:32.208 --> 1:14:34.500
-[fan screams]
-[flash bulbs clicking]

1:14:34.583 --> 1:14:36.583
Can I have a moment of your time, please?
Thank you.

1:14:36.666 --> 1:14:37.625
[bulb shatters]

1:14:37.708 --> 1:14:39.833
[gasps, laughs]

1:14:39.916 --> 1:14:43.208
[crowd continues chanting]
Marilyn! Marilyn! Marilyn!

1:14:44.583 --> 1:14:48.125
Marilyn! Marilyn! Marilyn!

1:14:50.291 --> 1:14:51.541
I've just learned.

1:14:52.666 --> 1:14:56.291
Be sure to go alone
to your hotel suite tonight.

1:14:56.375 --> 1:14:58.750
Someone special
will be waiting for you there.

1:15:00.583 --> 1:15:03.208
Someone special? Oh.

1:15:03.291 --> 1:15:06.416
-[crowd continues chanting] Marilyn!
-[dramatic music playing]

1:15:06.500 --> 1:15:07.416
Oh.

1:15:13.125 --> 1:15:14.291
Is it my father?

1:15:14.375 --> 1:15:16.875
[crowd cheering]

1:15:28.958 --> 1:15:32.791
Marilyn, tell our radio audience.
Are you lonely tonight?

1:15:34.333 --> 1:15:36.250
When are you two gonna get married?

1:15:37.291 --> 1:15:38.291
Married?

1:15:39.791 --> 1:15:40.625
No.

1:15:59.958 --> 1:16:02.041
Is he here? My father?

1:16:04.958 --> 1:16:08.041
It's like a happy ending
of a long, confused movie.

1:16:08.125 --> 1:16:09.166
Your father?

1:16:12.083 --> 1:16:14.375
I understand that I have a special date?

1:16:16.041 --> 1:16:18.958
After the party, in my hotel suite?

1:16:19.041 --> 1:16:21.041
[classical music playing]

1:16:25.916 --> 1:16:29.625
["Diamonds Are
a Girl's Best Friend" playing]

1:16:29.708 --> 1:16:34.541
♪ The French are glad to die for love ♪

1:16:34.625 --> 1:16:39.458
♪ They delight in fighting duels ♪

1:16:40.208 --> 1:16:43.916
♪ But I prefer a man who lives ♪

1:16:44.000 --> 1:16:50.958
♪ And gives expensive jewels ♪

1:16:51.041 --> 1:16:53.208
♪ A kiss on the hand ♪

1:16:53.291 --> 1:16:56.250
♪ May be quite continental ♪

1:16:56.333 --> 1:16:59.916
♪ But diamonds are a girl's best friend ♪

1:17:01.500 --> 1:17:03.958
♪ A kiss may be grand ♪

1:17:04.666 --> 1:17:08.375
♪ But it won't pay the rental
On your humble flat ♪

1:17:09.083 --> 1:17:12.125
♪ Or help you at the automat ♪

1:17:12.208 --> 1:17:16.875
♪ Men grow cold as girls grow old ♪

1:17:16.958 --> 1:17:21.250
♪ And we all lose our charms in the end ♪

1:17:22.333 --> 1:17:27.541
♪ But square-cut or pear-shaped
These rocks don't lose their shape ♪

1:17:27.625 --> 1:17:28.875
♪ Diamonds are a girl's… ♪

1:17:28.958 --> 1:17:30.125
Oh, Daddy.

1:17:32.208 --> 1:17:34.541
That thing up on the screen, it isn't me.

1:17:34.625 --> 1:17:35.625
♪ Tiffany's! ♪

1:17:39.416 --> 1:17:40.500
♪ Cartier! ♪

1:17:43.083 --> 1:17:44.500
♪ Black Starr ♪

1:17:44.583 --> 1:17:45.875
♪ Frost Gorham! ♪

1:17:45.958 --> 1:17:48.458
♪ Talk to me, Harry Winston
Tell me all about it! ♪

1:17:53.541 --> 1:17:58.583
♪ There may come a time
When a lass needs a lawyer ♪

1:17:58.666 --> 1:18:00.416
♪ But diamonds are a… ♪

1:18:00.500 --> 1:18:04.208
[crowd applauding, cheering]

1:18:20.833 --> 1:18:21.750
[exhales sharply]

1:18:22.875 --> 1:18:24.666
For this, you killed your baby?

1:18:33.500 --> 1:18:35.291
[breathing shakily]

1:18:41.916 --> 1:18:43.208
[exhales sharply]

1:18:45.083 --> 1:18:48.291
[ethereal music playing]

1:19:03.750 --> 1:19:04.750
Daddy?

1:19:14.375 --> 1:19:15.375
Baby.

1:19:20.791 --> 1:19:21.791
Oh, it's you.

1:19:31.458 --> 1:19:32.625
Marilyn, I…

1:19:34.416 --> 1:19:36.125
I just want you to be happy.

1:19:43.125 --> 1:19:44.375
I am happy.

1:19:45.875 --> 1:19:47.833
I've been happy all my life.

1:19:50.875 --> 1:19:52.375
Marilyn, we love each other.

1:19:54.708 --> 1:19:55.958
It's time we were married.

1:20:11.250 --> 1:20:12.583
Yes, I guess.

1:20:28.583 --> 1:20:32.500
Hey… Hey. Hey.

1:20:32.583 --> 1:20:34.416
I just love you so much.

1:20:39.250 --> 1:20:41.708
I just want to protect you
from all these jackals.

1:20:42.666 --> 1:20:44.750
I want to take you away from all of this.

1:20:48.208 --> 1:20:49.208
Yeah.

1:20:56.375 --> 1:21:00.916
In you, the world is born anew

1:21:02.291 --> 1:21:03.458
As two

1:21:05.583 --> 1:21:06.958
Before you

1:21:08.541 --> 1:21:10.083
There was but one

1:21:19.583 --> 1:21:21.083
-[chuckles]
-That's it, huh?

1:21:22.208 --> 1:21:23.708
-Is that the whole poem?
-Huh?

1:21:25.041 --> 1:21:27.125
-Yeah.
-Well, it's good, honey.

1:21:31.041 --> 1:21:31.875
[sighs]

1:21:38.166 --> 1:21:39.791
[Norma Jeane] People make spaghetti?

1:21:39.875 --> 1:21:41.500
-[chuckles]
-Mm-hmm. [chuckles]

1:21:41.583 --> 1:21:43.416
I mean, not just in a store?

1:21:44.750 --> 1:21:46.416
[woman speaking Italian]

1:21:49.875 --> 1:21:51.416
That smells delicious.

1:21:52.708 --> 1:21:54.291
[speaking Italian]

1:21:55.083 --> 1:21:56.000
Can I try it?

1:22:02.125 --> 1:22:03.416
Oh. Um…

1:22:04.500 --> 1:22:05.916
Is this to eat?

1:22:06.750 --> 1:22:08.125
I mean, standing up?

1:22:09.000 --> 1:22:10.291
[footsteps approaching]

1:22:13.416 --> 1:22:15.916
So, Marilyn,
what's it like being a movie star?

1:22:17.625 --> 1:22:18.541
Um…

1:22:19.041 --> 1:22:21.083
I'm not a star.

1:22:21.166 --> 1:22:23.000
I'm just some blonde. [chuckles]

1:22:24.041 --> 1:22:25.416
So the hair's real?

1:22:26.208 --> 1:22:27.416
No, no.

1:22:29.750 --> 1:22:32.125
[all laughing]

1:22:38.625 --> 1:22:40.875
[Norma Jeane] Daddy, it's so scary

1:22:41.625 --> 1:22:44.833
how a scene with actual people

1:22:46.166 --> 1:22:48.791
just goes on and on.

1:22:49.583 --> 1:22:50.791
Like on a bus.

1:22:54.208 --> 1:22:55.541
What's to stop it?

1:22:56.375 --> 1:22:57.208
Or…

1:22:58.875 --> 1:23:02.125
Or how to figure out what people mean

1:23:02.208 --> 1:23:04.500
when probably they don't mean anything.

1:23:05.000 --> 1:23:08.041
-[baseball bat cracks]
-[crowd cheering on TV]

1:23:08.125 --> 1:23:09.458
Not like a script.

1:23:10.916 --> 1:23:12.375
There's no point.

1:23:13.958 --> 1:23:14.916
[sighs]

1:23:15.000 --> 1:23:16.416
It just happens.

1:23:19.375 --> 1:23:20.791
Like the weather?

1:23:23.500 --> 1:23:24.416
Uh…

1:23:26.833 --> 1:23:28.583
You know, honey, in boxing,

1:23:30.250 --> 1:23:32.541
they say, "That got his attention"…

1:23:34.708 --> 1:23:36.416
when a guy gets hit hard.

1:23:38.250 --> 1:23:42.250
Well, it's about attention, honey.
It's about concentration.

1:23:44.000 --> 1:23:45.791
And if you don't have that…

1:24:00.833 --> 1:24:03.500
[announcer speaking indistinctly on TV]

1:24:23.083 --> 1:24:24.083
[grunts]

1:24:35.083 --> 1:24:37.125
I could have you hurt, you cocksuckers.

1:24:40.791 --> 1:24:42.291
-Hey, now.
-[chuckles]

1:24:43.833 --> 1:24:45.583
That's not the right attitude.

1:24:49.333 --> 1:24:51.583
I mean, we're on your side.

1:24:51.666 --> 1:24:54.708
And the lady's too. She's a real…

1:24:55.291 --> 1:24:56.958
High-class lady, in fact.

1:24:57.041 --> 1:24:58.208
[Eddy chuckles]

1:24:58.291 --> 1:25:01.375
What we feel, strongly,

1:25:01.458 --> 1:25:05.250
is that these, uh, negatives,
well, should be off the market.

1:25:07.000 --> 1:25:10.000
So they can't be misappropriated.

1:25:12.333 --> 1:25:13.291
[tires screeching]

1:25:23.166 --> 1:25:24.500
[breathing heavily]

1:25:25.625 --> 1:25:26.666
[dog barking]

1:25:34.083 --> 1:25:37.500
[Norma Jeane singing indistinctly
on recording]

1:25:39.583 --> 1:25:41.458
[grunting]

1:25:46.833 --> 1:25:47.958
Where the fuck is…

1:25:51.083 --> 1:25:53.000
Hi, Daddy. Where'd you go to?

1:25:53.500 --> 1:25:54.875
[Norma Jeane gasps, grunts]

1:26:00.541 --> 1:26:03.666
Oh, Daddy. It's my fault.

1:26:04.833 --> 1:26:08.333
I don't know how the room got this way.
I've been sick, I guess.

1:26:13.916 --> 1:26:16.916
Those photos. That's what you are. Meat.

1:26:20.166 --> 1:26:21.250
Daddy, no.

1:26:23.250 --> 1:26:24.916
I don't want to be.

1:26:27.416 --> 1:26:28.583
Tell them you won't.

1:26:29.500 --> 1:26:31.583
This new movie? No deal.

1:26:33.083 --> 1:26:34.750
Daddy, I have to work.

1:26:35.833 --> 1:26:37.250
It's my life.

1:26:39.000 --> 1:26:41.083
You tell them you want better roles.

1:26:42.333 --> 1:26:44.458
More serious roles.
You tell them you're quitting.

1:26:44.541 --> 1:26:47.458
You tell them
your husband says you're quitting.

1:26:48.416 --> 1:26:49.250
Yes.

1:26:50.833 --> 1:26:52.500
Yes, I will tell them.

1:27:15.500 --> 1:27:18.416
Don't you see how much I love you?
Don't you understand?

1:27:18.500 --> 1:27:19.791
I know.

1:27:21.916 --> 1:27:24.500
I can't bear to see you
cheapen yourself like that.

1:27:26.750 --> 1:27:30.458
[Norma Jeane] I just felt so sorry
for the creature at the end.

1:27:31.708 --> 1:27:33.416
"Sorry for the creature"?

1:27:33.916 --> 1:27:36.333
What'd you want him to do? Marry the girl?

1:27:36.416 --> 1:27:40.708
He was kind of scary-looking,
but he wasn't really all bad.

1:27:41.416 --> 1:27:44.541
I think he just craved a little affection,
you know?

1:27:44.625 --> 1:27:47.791
A sense of being loved
and needed and wanted.

1:27:48.666 --> 1:27:50.875
That's a very interesting point of view.

1:27:51.708 --> 1:27:56.791
[exclaims] You feel the breeze
from the subway? Isn't it delicious?

1:27:58.791 --> 1:28:00.750
Sort of cools the ankles, doesn't it?

1:28:02.916 --> 1:28:05.000
What do you think would be fun to do now?

1:28:05.500 --> 1:28:06.500
[director] And cut!

1:28:07.250 --> 1:28:10.208
[crowd cheering and whistling]

1:28:13.916 --> 1:28:17.416
[pensive music playing]

1:29:19.875 --> 1:29:21.375
Isn't it delicious?

1:29:21.458 --> 1:29:23.750
[whistling]

1:29:42.458 --> 1:29:45.416
[cheering and whistling continues]

1:30:36.000 --> 1:30:37.291
[breathing heavily]

1:30:39.250 --> 1:30:40.250
Daddy?

1:30:45.083 --> 1:30:47.666
Daddy, gosh, I'm sorry.

1:30:48.708 --> 1:30:50.875
-Keeping you waiting so long.
-There she is.

1:30:52.958 --> 1:30:55.250
You proud of yourself, hmm?

1:30:55.833 --> 1:30:56.708
[Norma Jeane] No.

1:30:56.791 --> 1:30:58.375
Are you proud of yourself, huh?

1:30:58.458 --> 1:31:00.791
-Daddy, don't…
-Don't touch me. Don't touch me.

1:31:00.875 --> 1:31:02.250
-Please…
-Proud of yourself?

1:31:02.333 --> 1:31:04.041
-What? Huh? Huh?
-No.

1:31:04.125 --> 1:31:06.541
-I'm workin' tomorrow.
-Showing off your crotch?

1:31:06.625 --> 1:31:08.000
-Please don't.
-Huh? Huh?

1:31:08.083 --> 1:31:11.333
You think that shit works on me?
Think that works on me? Oh, yeah?

1:31:11.416 --> 1:31:14.583
Everybody, they're gonna fuckin' know
what a fuckin' whore you are!

1:31:14.666 --> 1:31:17.000
Fuckin' get up! Huh? Huh?

1:31:17.083 --> 1:31:19.625
-[glass shatters]
-You fucking whore! Huh?

1:31:19.708 --> 1:31:22.625
-Get over here! Get over here!
-[Norma Jeane whimpers]

1:31:22.708 --> 1:31:24.541
[father] My dear daughter, Norma Jeane.

1:31:24.625 --> 1:31:25.541
[glass shatters]

1:31:26.416 --> 1:31:28.333
I did not see your new movie.

1:31:29.666 --> 1:31:32.791
Its vulgar title
and publicity attending it,

1:31:32.875 --> 1:31:35.166
these giant billboards
of your crude likeness

1:31:35.250 --> 1:31:36.833
posed with your dress lifted up

1:31:36.916 --> 1:31:39.416
for all the world
to see your private parts,

1:31:39.500 --> 1:31:41.791
did not make me wish to purchase a ticket.

1:31:45.625 --> 1:31:48.541
-[whipping]
-Fuckin'… Huh?

1:31:48.625 --> 1:31:50.875
[father] I had hoped to meet your husband.

1:31:51.375 --> 1:31:53.375
I've long been an admirer of his.

1:31:53.458 --> 1:31:54.458
[thudding]

1:31:54.958 --> 1:31:58.708
I was disappointed that your marriage
to such a stellar athlete

1:31:58.791 --> 1:32:01.750
ended in divorce and such ugly publicity.

1:32:04.416 --> 1:32:07.125
At least there are no children
to reap the shame.

1:32:33.708 --> 1:32:34.750
My Magda.

1:32:38.500 --> 1:32:39.625
My Magda.

1:32:41.208 --> 1:32:44.916
Magda. Magda. Magda.

1:32:45.000 --> 1:32:48.708
Magda. Magda. Magda.

1:32:50.916 --> 1:32:52.000
Magda.

1:32:55.458 --> 1:32:57.916
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

1:33:40.750 --> 1:33:41.833
Marilyn Monroe?

1:33:44.166 --> 1:33:45.083
Here?

1:33:47.750 --> 1:33:49.500
Magda? Her?

1:33:50.875 --> 1:33:55.375
"When I dream of back there,
I dream of the smell of laundry."

1:33:56.708 --> 1:34:02.500
"The tub overflowing and the poem I wrote,
'Magda,' floating, soaked."

1:34:03.416 --> 1:34:05.375
"I'm frantically trying
to collect the pages

1:34:05.458 --> 1:34:08.708
before the ink runs in streaks
and the poem comes apart in my hands."

1:34:08.791 --> 1:34:09.625
Oh.

1:34:10.541 --> 1:34:11.875
He's in love with her.

1:34:12.750 --> 1:34:14.500
[man] "These words I wrote her…"

1:34:14.583 --> 1:34:16.333
"Two hundred words."

1:34:16.416 --> 1:34:19.208
"A kind of… prayer."

1:34:21.041 --> 1:34:24.208
"And I wake in Brooklyn,
nearly 40 years later,

1:34:24.291 --> 1:34:25.916
my heart knocking in my chest."

1:34:27.125 --> 1:34:29.666
"And I remember her face, blushing,

1:34:30.750 --> 1:34:34.416
and her beautiful wide-set eyes
looking up from the poem, and saying…"

1:34:37.625 --> 1:34:38.625
[inhales sharply]

1:34:40.666 --> 1:34:42.000
Not my Magda.

1:34:42.708 --> 1:34:45.291
[applause]

1:36:03.083 --> 1:36:05.916
[playwright] Magda was my own first love.

1:36:08.916 --> 1:36:10.416
Never consummated.

1:36:12.541 --> 1:36:14.708
Never even really declared. [chuckles]

1:36:16.208 --> 1:36:17.041
Um…

1:36:18.958 --> 1:36:20.208
She would be,

1:36:21.958 --> 1:36:25.750
if she was even still alive,
in her… in her mid-fifties.

1:36:28.541 --> 1:36:29.791
Beautiful Magda.

1:36:31.166 --> 1:36:32.125
Middle-aged.

1:36:41.833 --> 1:36:42.666
I…

1:36:43.916 --> 1:36:47.416
I had some ideas about Magda,

1:36:48.416 --> 1:36:49.708
if you're interested.

1:36:51.875 --> 1:36:53.375
Of course I'm interested.

1:36:55.791 --> 1:36:57.291
It's very good of you to care.

1:37:00.750 --> 1:37:07.166
Um, this girl, Magda,
she's like Natasha in The Three Sisters.

1:37:07.250 --> 1:37:10.166
The one they laugh at
because her dress is the wrong color.

1:37:10.791 --> 1:37:13.416
Except, with Magda,
it's the way she speaks English.

1:37:16.500 --> 1:37:18.208
Who told you that?

1:37:20.875 --> 1:37:21.708
What?

1:37:23.500 --> 1:37:26.333
About The Three Sisters and my play?

1:37:33.375 --> 1:37:35.458
-Nobody.
-Kazan?

1:37:37.291 --> 1:37:38.916
That I'd been influenced?

1:37:40.625 --> 1:37:41.833
Uh, no.

1:37:44.250 --> 1:37:47.375
No, I read the play myself.

1:37:48.833 --> 1:37:50.125
I always thought I…

1:37:54.208 --> 1:37:56.583
I always thought I could play Natasha.

1:38:02.750 --> 1:38:08.416
I was thinking,
what Chekhov does with Natasha, he… he…

1:38:08.500 --> 1:38:10.791
[clears throat] He… he surprises you,

1:38:12.166 --> 1:38:16.083
because Natasha turns out to be
so strong and devious.

1:38:17.125 --> 1:38:18.208
And cruel.

1:38:20.166 --> 1:38:24.125
But your Magda, she never changes much.

1:38:24.208 --> 1:38:25.916
She's always so good.

1:38:26.000 --> 1:38:27.000
Yes.

1:38:28.041 --> 1:38:29.125
Magda is good.

1:38:29.958 --> 1:38:31.500
Was good. The original.

1:38:34.000 --> 1:38:36.291
She wouldn't dream of being cruel.

1:38:39.375 --> 1:38:40.208
Yeah.

1:38:44.000 --> 1:38:48.541
And, uh, you have
any other thoughts about Magda?

1:38:52.791 --> 1:38:53.625
Hmm?

1:38:59.833 --> 1:39:01.250
One thing I was thinking,

1:39:02.708 --> 1:39:04.458
Magda wouldn't know how to read.

1:39:05.666 --> 1:39:08.916
Isaac shows his poem to her,
and she's only pretending to read it.

1:39:09.833 --> 1:39:10.666
[gasps]

1:39:14.250 --> 1:39:15.458
Oh my God.

1:39:18.125 --> 1:39:20.250
She was illiterate. That's what it was.

1:39:24.333 --> 1:39:25.291
Of course.

1:39:28.875 --> 1:39:31.083
Well, thank you. Thank you.

1:39:32.250 --> 1:39:33.083
[sniffles]

1:39:37.708 --> 1:39:39.083
Uh, what…

1:39:39.916 --> 1:39:43.416
I… I suppose I should call you Marilyn,
shouldn't I?

1:39:46.250 --> 1:39:48.000
Or is that just a stage name?

1:39:48.083 --> 1:39:49.250
[chuckles]

1:39:49.333 --> 1:39:50.791
You could call me Norma.

1:39:51.916 --> 1:39:53.291
That's my true name.

1:39:54.500 --> 1:39:57.250
I could call you Norma, if you prefer.

1:39:59.958 --> 1:40:02.833
Or, uh, I could call you, uh…

1:40:05.000 --> 1:40:06.041
my Magda.

1:40:10.041 --> 1:40:11.083
I'd like that.

1:40:12.083 --> 1:40:13.541
My secret Magda.

1:40:14.541 --> 1:40:15.375
Yes.

1:40:16.333 --> 1:40:19.416
But maybe "Marilyn" when others are around

1:40:19.500 --> 1:40:22.083
so there wouldn't be
any misunderstandings.

1:40:22.166 --> 1:40:25.125
When others are around,
it doesn't matter what you call me.

1:40:25.208 --> 1:40:26.375
You can whistle.

1:40:27.250 --> 1:40:29.250
You can call me, "Hey, you."

1:40:33.708 --> 1:40:34.791
Hey, you.

1:40:38.291 --> 1:40:39.291
Hey, you.

1:40:43.000 --> 1:40:45.291
[fanfare playing]

1:40:45.375 --> 1:40:47.416
[announcer] Putting an end
to all speculation,

1:40:47.500 --> 1:40:52.166
Arthur Miller and Marilyn Monroe
confirmed they will soon marry.

1:40:52.250 --> 1:40:55.333
[reporter] Could you tell us what kind
of a wedding you're going to have?

1:40:55.416 --> 1:40:57.333
Very quiet, I hope.

1:40:57.416 --> 1:41:00.375
[peaceful music playing]

1:41:01.583 --> 1:41:02.583
[laughing]

1:41:03.750 --> 1:41:05.916
Daddy, this is so beautiful!

1:41:06.750 --> 1:41:08.333
I don't ever wanna leave!

1:41:10.500 --> 1:41:12.083
[laughs] St…

1:41:13.125 --> 1:41:14.083
[shrieks]

1:41:14.166 --> 1:41:15.833
[both laughing]

1:41:27.250 --> 1:41:28.750
It's so beautiful.

1:41:31.208 --> 1:41:32.083
[chuckles]

1:41:32.875 --> 1:41:34.208
Oh, Daddy!

1:41:36.166 --> 1:41:37.666
I don't ever want to leave.

1:41:46.458 --> 1:41:47.666
[shrieks]

1:42:14.708 --> 1:42:15.916
I love you.

1:42:25.500 --> 1:42:26.708
We love you.

1:42:28.333 --> 1:42:30.833
[peaceful music continues]

1:42:51.875 --> 1:42:53.000
Daddy, come on.

1:42:54.583 --> 1:42:58.083
Baby's hungry. He wants his mama to eat.

1:42:58.166 --> 1:42:59.333
[Arthur] Mm, yeah?

1:43:00.000 --> 1:43:00.833
[exclaims]

1:43:03.000 --> 1:43:04.000
[chuckles]

1:43:04.083 --> 1:43:05.708
Baby makes his wishes known.

1:43:06.375 --> 1:43:07.750
Norma's just the vessel.

1:43:08.541 --> 1:43:10.375
[chuckles] Okay.

1:43:10.458 --> 1:43:11.583
[laughing]

1:43:11.666 --> 1:43:13.708
Not after those potatoes. [chuckles]

1:43:19.291 --> 1:43:20.125
[chuckles]

1:43:22.583 --> 1:43:24.458
Am I your good girl, Daddy?

1:43:27.250 --> 1:43:29.666
Yeah. You're my good girl, darling.

1:43:35.125 --> 1:43:36.125
Come here.

1:43:38.791 --> 1:43:40.458
You're my only love.

1:43:42.416 --> 1:43:44.833
[peaceful music playing]

1:44:36.000 --> 1:44:40.125
[Norma Jeane] Daddy, you won't ever
write about me, will you?

1:44:41.333 --> 1:44:43.666
[Arthur] Darling, of course not.

1:44:45.833 --> 1:44:47.291
Why would I do such a thing?

1:44:47.375 --> 1:44:49.083
[Norma Jeane] It's what people do.

1:44:50.291 --> 1:44:51.208
Sometimes.

1:44:52.541 --> 1:44:53.416
Writers.

1:44:54.625 --> 1:44:56.333
[Arthur] I'm not other people.

1:44:57.166 --> 1:44:58.875
You and I are not other people.

1:45:07.791 --> 1:45:08.708
Darling,

1:45:09.625 --> 1:45:11.666
where do you go when you disappear?

1:45:18.375 --> 1:45:19.208
Daddy…

1:45:23.958 --> 1:45:25.625
Don't make me go back.

1:45:28.208 --> 1:45:29.458
[breathing shakily]

1:45:29.541 --> 1:45:31.583
I never wanna be her again.

1:45:37.291 --> 1:45:41.583
I got out with my life last time
but only just barely.

1:45:45.458 --> 1:45:47.208
[Arthur] Yeah, she's wonderful.

1:45:48.833 --> 1:45:50.958
Yeah, pregnancy agrees with her.

1:45:52.250 --> 1:45:54.625
Even morning sickness,
she's cheerful about.

1:45:56.500 --> 1:45:57.916
And then she says, "Oh!"

1:45:58.583 --> 1:46:02.250
"Well, this is how
it's supposed to be, I guess." [chuckles]

1:46:05.000 --> 1:46:08.875
Yeah. Esther was always so cruel.

1:46:10.625 --> 1:46:12.625
It wouldn't occur to Norma to be cruel.

1:46:15.958 --> 1:46:18.041
If I have one regret… [sighs]

1:46:19.291 --> 1:46:21.458
…it's that time passes so quickly.

1:46:26.041 --> 1:46:26.916
[groans]

1:46:32.875 --> 1:46:35.083
[baby] You won't hurt me
this time, will you?

1:46:36.916 --> 1:46:40.500
Not do what you did the last time?

1:46:43.916 --> 1:46:45.041
I didn't.

1:46:48.583 --> 1:46:51.833
-I didn't mean to.
-[baby] Yes, you meant to.

1:46:52.333 --> 1:46:53.541
It was your decision.

1:46:58.416 --> 1:47:00.416
You're not the same baby.

1:47:02.458 --> 1:47:03.916
You're this baby.

1:47:04.750 --> 1:47:08.208
[baby] That was me. It's always me.

1:47:09.083 --> 1:47:10.500
[Norma Jeane shushes]

1:47:13.166 --> 1:47:14.458
He loves us.

1:47:17.875 --> 1:47:19.208
He would die for us.

1:47:20.541 --> 1:47:21.833
He said so.

1:47:26.625 --> 1:47:28.791
Flowers make people feel welcome.

1:47:30.291 --> 1:47:31.708
Like they're wanted.

1:47:34.791 --> 1:47:36.541
[faucet running]

1:47:56.208 --> 1:47:59.208
Mm, darling, you cut 'em
a little too short. See?

1:48:01.083 --> 1:48:02.000
[sighs]

1:48:03.083 --> 1:48:05.458
What did I… What?

1:48:07.625 --> 1:48:10.750
Well, don't worry,
we can repair the damage. Hmm?

1:48:12.666 --> 1:48:13.625
Come here.

1:48:16.750 --> 1:48:18.291
[man] Where's Norma gone to?

1:48:20.041 --> 1:48:24.166
She's absolutely adorable.
She's nothing like I expected.

1:48:25.000 --> 1:48:26.208
She's so well-read.

1:48:26.291 --> 1:48:29.291
[woman] Yeah, like she's read
Rudy's book. [laughs]

1:48:29.375 --> 1:48:31.291
I'm just glad somebody has.

1:48:32.458 --> 1:48:36.166
[woman] Look at that out there.
Oh my God. Do you guys see that?

1:48:36.250 --> 1:48:37.458
This is incredible.

1:48:47.166 --> 1:48:48.166
Darling…

1:48:49.875 --> 1:48:52.250
Aren't you gonna come down
to the beach with us?

1:48:53.500 --> 1:48:55.000
Why you hiding in here?

1:49:02.750 --> 1:49:06.458
I'm coming, Daddy. I was just…

1:49:06.541 --> 1:49:10.541
Darling, it isn't necessary
to make so much of this visit.

1:49:10.625 --> 1:49:12.041
You know Rudy and Jean.

1:49:19.125 --> 1:49:20.541
But they don't like me.

1:49:21.583 --> 1:49:22.958
They've come to see you.

1:49:24.833 --> 1:49:27.916
Norma, stop being so ridiculous.

1:49:29.000 --> 1:49:31.000
You know they've come to see us both.

1:49:34.375 --> 1:49:38.458
Darling, come down there with me,
huh, will ya? They're waiting.

1:49:45.208 --> 1:49:46.041
Hey.

1:49:48.000 --> 1:49:49.208
Come out there with me.

1:49:51.250 --> 1:49:53.000
You're looking very beautiful.

1:49:53.541 --> 1:49:54.375
Hmm?

1:49:56.458 --> 1:49:59.541
-Come, yeah? Come.
-[clears throat]

1:50:03.500 --> 1:50:04.791
You all right, darling?

1:50:04.875 --> 1:50:05.875
[waves crashing]

1:50:10.000 --> 1:50:12.083
I'll bring them the beer. [clears throat]

1:50:20.583 --> 1:50:21.666
[chuckles]

1:50:26.083 --> 1:50:27.208
[they exclaim]

1:50:31.416 --> 1:50:33.708
[Norma Jeane] I'm okay. [chuckles]

1:50:33.791 --> 1:50:34.791
I'm okay.

1:50:35.833 --> 1:50:36.750
[sighs]

1:50:49.916 --> 1:50:51.208
[breathing heavily]

1:50:59.708 --> 1:51:00.791
[sobs] Help me.

1:51:02.166 --> 1:51:04.791
Help me. Save my baby.

1:51:05.458 --> 1:51:09.208
Please, Daddy, help me! Deliver the baby!

1:51:10.125 --> 1:51:12.625
-Daddy! Daddy, help!
